article.headline: Southern beats Alabama A&M 73-52 for 6th straight win

images.name: A. Rodgers made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by C. Hyder.
images.caption: 1H (5:55) SOU Adrian Rodgers made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Christopher Hyder.

article.linkText: Southern beats Alabama A&M 73-52 for 6th straight win
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- Adrian Rodgers scored 20 points, Christopher Hyder added 14 and Southern beat Alabama A&M 73-52 on Monday night for the Jaguars' sixth consecutive victory. Rashad Andrews and Trelun Banks added 10 points apiece for Southern (14-7, 6-2 Southwestern Athletic). It was tied at 20-all before Southern closed the first half on a 16-5 spurt for a 36-25 lead. Quinterian McConico's jumper pulled Alabama A&M to 44-35, but Rodgers and Andrews answered with back-to-back 3-pointers and Southern led by double figures the rest of the way. Two free throws by D'Arian Allen extended Southern's lead to 20 points with 5:25 left. McConico led Alabama A&M (6-10, 2-5) with 12 points and Nicholas West had 10. The Bulldogs were held to 17-of-51 shooting (33 percent) from the field and hit just 14 of 24 free throws.
